                <h1>Understanding the Bull Skeleton: Anatomy & Significance</h1>
                <p>Bull skeletons are fascinating remnants of one of nature's most powerful animals. Composed of bones like the skull, vertebrae, and ribs, these skeletons offer insight into the bull's strength and agility. They are often used in educational settings or as decorative elements, symbolizing resilience and vitality in various cultures.</p>
